feat: add case-centric legal practice management system

Transform HeyAmin from a tool-centric app into a case-centric platform
where every feature serves a lawyer's daily work managing clients and cases.

Phase 1 - Database models and migration:
- Client, Case, CaseDocument, CaseNote, CaseEvent SQLAlchemy models
- Alembic migration for all five tables with indexes and FK cascades

Phase 2 - API routes:
- /api/v1/clients CRUD with search, filters, pagination
- /api/v1/cases CRUD with dashboard stats, documents, notes, timeline
- Active case tracking via Redis, background Amin briefing generation

Phase 3 - Amin context integration:
- build_case_context() injects active case into every Amin conversation
- Three new tools: file_to_case, get_case_context, set_case_deadline
- Workflow execution canvas shows case banner and logs step completions

Phase 4 - Navigation overhaul:
- Redesigned Rail1 icons (Home, Clients, Cases, Workflows, Documents, Intelligence)
- New ClientsPanel and CasesPanel for Rail2
- Updated HomePanel with case-centric dashboard (due soon, stats, quick actions)
- Restructured AdminPanel and IntelligencePanel

Phase 5 - New pages:
- /dashboard with case stats, Amin briefing, active cases table
- /clients listing with search/filters and NewClientModal
- /clients/[id] detail with metadata and associated cases
- /cases listing with priority/status filters and NewCaseModal
- /cases/[id] detail with documents, notes, timeline, workflows tabs

Phase 6 - Integration connections:
- Screen context auto-enriched with active case data globally
- Layout fetches active case on auth for cross-page availability
- Document detail page: Attach to Case button
- Research page: case banner and jurisdiction pre-fill
- Workflow launch page: case banner and case-aware start button
